20:01.700 --> 20:02.740
Mr. Deen.

20:04.780 --> 20:06.080
Tom Friedman?

20:06.450 --> 20:08.950
Oh, my gosh,
I can’t believe it.

20:09.080 --> 20:10.580
What’s it been, 20 years?

20:10.830 --> 20:12.000
Yeah, at least.

20:12.170 --> 20:13.000
Well, what are you doing?

20:13.130 --> 20:14.330
Are you at the
Garden Spot still?

20:14.460 --> 20:15.960
Yeah, yep, I’m still there.

20:17.000 --> 20:17.920
I’m still there.

20:18.460 --> 20:20.590
I’m not leaving till
they name something after me.

20:20.880 --> 20:23.260
So, what are you
doing in here today?

20:47.910 --> 20:49.160
You gonna yell at me, Mr. Deen?

20:49.540 --> 20:50.910
No, of course not.

20:52.620 --> 20:54.790
You don’t belong here, Nate.
We’re gonna get you out.

20:55.420 --> 20:56.670
All right?

20:57.630 --> 20:59.300
Do you have
any family I can call?

21:02.590 --> 21:03.380
No one?

21:04.340 --> 21:05.140
No.

21:07.300 --> 21:07.970
Who were you living with

21:08.100 --> 21:09.770
before you went
into foster care?

21:10.890 --> 21:12.390
-My nanny and grandpa.
-Okay.

21:12.640 --> 21:15.150
That-- it’s been a
very long time, Mr. Deen.

21:15.480 --> 21:17.860
I don’t think they’d want
to help, if they’re still alive.

21:18.730 --> 21:21.400
Well, we’re gonna
give it a try. All right?

21:25.610 --> 21:27.660
Nate, I need a name.

21:30.290 --> 21:31.290
Cole.

21:31.410 --> 21:32.830
C-O-L-E?

21:33.160 --> 21:35.920
Yeah, they’re up
in Lebanon. They were.

21:36.040 --> 21:37.210
All right.

21:38.210 --> 21:40.050
We’ll find a
way to get you out.

21:42.170 --> 21:43.920
Sorry for wasting
your time, Mr. Deen.

21:44.630 --> 21:45.840
