01:04:33.620 --> 01:04:36.660
♪ I’m gonna let it shine ♪

01:04:38.910 --> 01:04:41.870
♪ This little light of mine ♪

01:04:43.750 --> 01:04:46.500
♪ I’m gonna let it shine ♪

01:04:47.920 --> 01:04:50.630
♪ This little light of mine ♪

01:04:55.300 --> 01:04:56.970
Okay, good night.

01:04:57.140 --> 01:04:58.140
Farewell.

01:04:58.270 --> 01:04:59.930
God knows when
we shall meet again.

01:05:00.180 --> 01:05:01.520
Actually, I do.

01:05:01.690 --> 01:05:02.650
Tomorrow night at seven,

01:05:02.940 --> 01:05:04.060
stagger-through of act one.

01:05:05.400 --> 01:05:06.650
Bye, Mr. Deen.

01:05:06.770 --> 01:05:08.190
Good night, Mr. D.

01:05:08.650 --> 01:05:09.740
Bye.

01:05:09.900 --> 01:05:10.650
Good job today.

01:05:12.410 --> 01:05:13.070
Bye.

01:05:13.200 --> 01:05:14.120
Can I talk to you
for a second?

01:05:14.660 --> 01:05:16.080
I can’t see you anymore, Nate.

01:05:16.200 --> 01:05:17.030
What part of that
don’t you understand?

01:05:17.160 --> 01:05:18.290
-Just let me explain.
-Explain what?

01:05:18.490 --> 01:05:21.370
You were arrested,
and now you’re a changed man.

01:05:22.750 --> 01:05:24.210
You’re going back to prison.

01:05:24.380 --> 01:05:26.960
Yeah for,
for a few days, Tina.

01:05:28.090 --> 01:05:29.380
Then it will be done with.

01:05:29.510 --> 01:05:30.300
Stage
light’s going out.

01:05:30.550 --> 01:05:34.800
Okay, just
leave me alone, Nathan.

01:05:40.140 --> 01:05:41.350
Tina.

01:05:42.770 --> 01:05:43.640
Tina!

01:05:43.980 --> 01:05:46.150
Come on, can
we just talk, please?

01:05:46.270 --> 01:05:46.980
No, we can’t talk.

01:05:47.110 --> 01:05:47.980
-Tina!
-What?

01:05:48.110 --> 01:05:48.860
Come on.

01:05:48.980 --> 01:05:49.690
Ow!

01:05:49.820 --> 01:05:52.110
Stop! What are you doing?

01:05:52.450 --> 01:05:54.780
Tina,
get in the car.

01:05:54.910 --> 01:05:55.950
Daddy, we weren’t even--

01:05:56.070 --> 01:05:57.780
Get in the car!

01:06:01.160 --> 01:06:03.120
Nathan, stay
away from Tina, okay?

01:06:03.580 --> 01:06:05.750
So don’t talk to
her, don’t touch her,

01:06:05.880 --> 01:06:08.130
just stay the hell
away from my daughter, got it?

01:06:10.420 --> 01:06:11.880
Nathan, do we
understand each other?

01:06:12.010 --> 01:06:13.380
Yeah, okay, I get it.

01:06:17.760 --> 01:06:20.310
It’s only
for 72 hours, okay?

01:06:21.020 --> 01:06:23.100
Call me when you’re
ready for me to pick you up.

01:06:23.730 --> 01:06:24.390
And remember--

01:06:24.520 --> 01:06:25.480
Don’t.

01:06:25.770 --> 01:06:26.900
Don’t say it, Stan.

01:06:40.410 --> 01:06:41.830
Nathan...

01:06:47.290 --> 01:06:48.290
Nathan.

01:06:49.750 --> 01:06:52.590
♪ I’m gonna let it shine ♪

01:07:11.360 --> 01:07:14.860
Okay, listen,
Tina, when you cross downstage,

01:07:14.990 --> 01:07:16.900
don’t cross in
front of Barnaby, okay?

01:07:17.030 --> 01:07:18.740
All right, let’s
take it from your entrance.

01:07:18.860 --> 01:07:21.030
-All right, and Barnaby?
-Yeah.

01:07:21.160 --> 01:07:24.040
I’m about ready to give
my doctor his marching orders

01:07:24.160 --> 01:07:25.500
and sign up with you.

01:07:26.000 --> 01:07:26.870
Thanks, Mr. D.

01:07:27.040 --> 01:07:28.830
I take Blue Cross
and Blue Shield.

01:07:29.000 --> 01:07:30.460
Okay, good for you.

01:07:30.670 --> 01:07:31.500
Okay, here we go.

01:07:31.750 --> 01:07:34.420
And remember,
project, project, project.

01:07:34.550 --> 01:07:35.260
Yes, sir.

01:07:35.380 --> 01:07:36.800
It’s really
coming along, Stan.

01:07:37.170 --> 01:07:37.930
Oh, thanks.

01:07:38.180 --> 01:07:39.010
Yeah.

01:07:39.390 --> 01:07:41.430
John asked me to come down
and speak with you for a minute.

01:07:41.970 --> 01:07:42.810
Okay.

01:07:43.560 --> 01:07:44.850
Guys, take five.

01:07:47.690 --> 01:07:48.850
We have a problem.

01:07:56.940 --> 01:07:58.700
-It sucked.
-Good.

01:07:59.490 --> 01:08:01.120
It wasn’t supposed
to be the Ritz.

01:08:02.580 --> 01:08:04.120
I have some bad news for you.

01:08:04.620 --> 01:08:05.540
It’s about Tina.

01:08:06.000 --> 01:08:07.040
She’s out of bounds.

01:08:07.580 --> 01:08:08.660
That’s not fair, Stan.

01:08:08.790 --> 01:08:09.870
Nate, look
at the big picture.

01:08:10.000 --> 01:08:11.540
No, I get it.
I get it.

01:08:12.460 --> 01:08:13.670
Help me, Stan.

01:08:14.460 --> 01:08:15.670
I like her. I have...

01:08:16.420 --> 01:08:18.130
real feelings for her.
How do I handle that?

01:08:18.260 --> 01:08:19.630
I can’t just make them go away.

01:08:53.210 --> 01:08:54.000
I will.

01:08:54.710 --> 01:08:56.250
It may not
have very long...

01:09:37.460 --> 01:09:39.460
I’m gonna catch you,
later.

01:09:39.590 --> 01:09:41.630
Hey, would you,
would you wait a minute?

01:09:41.760 --> 01:09:42.680
What?

01:09:43.090 --> 01:09:44.680
I just, I brought you flowers.

01:09:44.930 --> 01:09:47.430
I wanted to say
you did a great job.

01:09:47.680 --> 01:09:49.140
I know you can’t talk
to me anymore or whatever,

01:09:49.270 --> 01:09:52.600
but I thought you should know
how great you were on stage.

01:09:53.440 --> 01:09:56.400
Hey, I’ve,
I’ve turned it around.

01:09:57.190 --> 01:09:58.730
Okay, I have, and I
know your dad doesn’t want us

01:09:58.860 --> 01:09:59.570
talking anymore or whatever.

01:09:59.690 --> 01:10:01.240
It’s not my
dad, Nathan, okay?

01:10:02.150 --> 01:10:02.950
It’s me.

01:10:04.070 --> 01:10:05.910
Great show, man.
You killed it.

01:10:06.160 --> 01:10:07.950
-Congrats.
-Thank you so much.

01:10:08.450 --> 01:10:09.660
Thank you, so much.

01:10:09.790 --> 01:10:10.740
I picked them out
myself, right?

01:10:11.000 --> 01:10:12.080
They’re beautiful.

01:10:12.830 --> 01:10:14.160
-Thank you.
